{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, topics such as aggregation or the theory of soft probability are less developed at present.",
    "Soft graphs [11] and their extensions to fuzzy soft graphs [12] and intuitionistic fuzzy soft graphs [212] are beyond the scope of this summary of literature.",
    "Other soft algebraic structuresIn addition to topology, algebraic structures such as groups or (semi)rings have been exported to the soft setting.",
    "These extensions produced soft groups [29,30], soft semirings [101], and soft rings [5].",
    "Feng et al. [104] demonstrated the applicability of soft binary relations to the theory of semigroups and [248] defined soft rough hemirings, which they utilized for multi-attribute multi-person decisionmaking."
  ]
}